\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f42\fs22\insrsid2717339\charrsid1732375 W.M.:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\fs22\insrsid2717339   \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\fs22\insrsid12849482\charrsid7821535 Well, it was a Master
\rquote s, because, in those days, you couldn\rquote t \'85 the only way you could do a Ph.D. in the Humanities, in Wales, was do the Master\rquote 
s first, which took two years, and then you did the Ph.D. after, which took three years.  So it actually took you five years to get a Ph.D., and Ph.D.\rquote s were very very unusual in the non-sciences, so I did the Masters, and this was Alwyn\rquote 
s idea.  And \'85 well, it wasn\rquote t so much \'85 well, yes, I wanted to become an academic.  I realised, early on, that I wanted to become an academic, so I saw the Masters as a passport to becoming a lecturer in a university.
