t want my contract to be renewed.  So they asked me if I\rquote d do an extra year so that my successor, \'85\'85\'85\'85.. (INAUDIBLE \endash  445) the Chief Executive of the Steel Company in Wales, could take over.  And I said, \'93Yes\'94
.  And that was a mistake actually, because it doesn\rquote t \'85\'85\'85\'85. (INAUDIBLE \endash  450), it didn\rquote t work.  I would say to him, \'93Look, you are asphyxiating the \'85 you do it\'94.  And he\rquote d say, \'93No, no, you\rquote 
re still the Chairman, and I\rquote m only a member at the moment\'94, so we had an uneasy \'85 and that coincided with the Kenneth Clark reforms and things like this, money following the patient and so on, so I was glad to get out.  But I\rquote d \'85
 even if there hadn\rquote t been those changes, I think I\rquote d had enough.  And, of course, the other thing about it is that it\rquote s pretty insidious.  After a while, I wasn\rquote t doing as much reading as I should have done
