d spend all Sunday just working my way through policy documents and circulars and things like this.  There was no alternative, I just had to do it.  And then Chris or somebody would say, \'93Have you seen, you know, the book by so and so?\'94  And I
\rquote d say, \'93No, no\'94.  \'93Oh\'94, he said, \'93You must read it\'94.  It must be very good.  And I really never got round to reading it.  Or if I read that, I would miss something else.  You know, I simply \'85
 the academic interest, at any rate, I didn\rquote t update my lectures as much as I should have.
