rown away.  So I was employed by the Ministry of Defence, National Guard, Ministry of the Interior, to do projects, which I did, and I enjoyed that very much, although I\rquote 
d no expectations about the results ever being used, because it would either put expatr
iates out of jobs, or whatever!  And that then led to doing a Masters Course on Health Services Management, and that also led to offering the same course in Singapore, Hong Kong, and Kuala Lumpur.  So I did that, and I\rquote 
d given up my Chair, and I did a lot of teaching, and a lot of consultancy work, which I really really enjoyed, until I got to the point where I realised, when we\rquote d move to East Anglia, that in one year, I\rquote d only spent eight weeks at home.

